President Joe Biden and First Lady Jill Biden are set to host President Emmanuel Macron and Mrs. Brigitte Macron of France for a State Visit to the United States on December 1, 2022. This will be the first State Visit of the Biden-Harris Administration and will highlight the strong relationship between the two countries. The visit will focus on areas such as shared democratic values, economic ties, defense, and security cooperation. The leaders will also discuss global challenges and areas of mutual interest.